text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus subsericea is the accepted name of a tree species in the Asian sub-genus of 'ring-cupped oaks' and the family Fagaceae; there are no known subspecies.This oak species is an emergent tropical forest tree, growing up to 52 m. tall and 0.86 m. dbh and has been recorded from Malaysia, Indonesia, Philippines (Palawan).
